description.narrative:
Global Rights Alert (GRA) is a non-for profit Non-governmental organization registered under the laws of Uganda. The organization'sMission is; To Make natural resources benefit the people.GRAs work is rooted in empowering communities to negotiate for equitable benefit sharing, influence decisions that impact their lives, and mitigate human rights abuses associated with the exploitation of natural resources. on this project, GRA will lead the primary research component of the project. GRAs tasks will be;
A) Take part inthe preparatory training on the research methodology to be applied on this study B) Mapping/identifying the route (districts, sub-counties, villages) expected to host the EACOP project that will provide a road map for the process of assessment. C) Take part initial consultations with relevant institutions of government of Uganda, local government, oil companies to prepare for undertaking the full HRIA. D) Develop criteria for selecting communities to be engaged in the HRIA in consultation with Oxfam and the lead consultant.
E) Adapting the #Getting it Right Tool# to develop specific data collection tools, train and oversee collection of primary data. F) Train community monitors on using the data collection tool (in partnership with Oxfam) G) Undertake pre-testing of the data collection tools in at least three selected communities along the proposed route. H) Undertake data cleaning, analysis, compile and submit draft report. I) Review the combined country report consisting of secondary and primary data sections. J) Participate in validation of the research findings and address comments arising from the same. K) Compile the final study report. L) Take part in joint advocacy efforts with Oxfam in Uganda country office and CRED, using results from the research
